Hi there,

Today we announced our new series of models, OpenAI o1. We’ve developed these models to spend more time thinking before they respond. They can reason through complex tasks and solve harder problems than previous models in science, coding, and math. Read more in our blog post ( https://openai.com/index/introducing-openai-o1-preview/ ).

You can try the o1 beta in ChatGPT Plus ( https://chatgpt.com/ ). We’re rolling out two models:

* Our larger model, o1-preview, which has strong reasoning capabilities and broad world knowledge.
* Our smaller model, o1-mini, which is faster and is competitive with o1-preview at coding tasks (you can see how it performs here ( https://openai.com/index/openai-o1-mini-advancing-cost-efficient-reasoning/ ) ).

These models aren’t available in the API for your account while we’re in this short beta period. (Developers on usage tier 5 ( https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/rate-limits/usage-tiers ) will have access, but we’ll expand access to more tiers.) We’re continuing to improve o1 and we’ll be in touch as soon as it’s available to you in the API.

Best,
The OpenAI team

